Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Halve, peel, and finely chop
@shallot{1}. Mince @garlic{2%clove}. Crush @black peppercorns{1/2%ounce} in their bag with
a #mallet{} or heavy pan until coarsely ground. Cut @baby potatoes{12%ounce} into quarters,
then toss with a drizzle of @Colavita extra virgin olive oil{1%teaspoon} and a pinch
of @salt{1%pinch} and @pepper{pinch} on a #baking sheet{}. Roast in oven until browned,
about ~{20%minutes}.

Halve, core, and chop @Fuji apple{1} into ½-inch pieces. Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a
#medium pot{} over medium heat. Add half the garlic and cook until fragrant,
~{30%seconds}. Add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce} and cook until no longer crisp,
~{3-4%minutes}, tossing occasionally. Stir in apple and cook until just softened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in ½ cup water and half the @gluten free chicken demi glace{1} and
@vegetable oil{1%teaspoon}. Increase heat to medium-high and bring to a simmer. Cook
until liquid is evaporated and apples and cabbage are very tender, ~{4-5%minutes},
stirring occasionally. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from heat and
cover until rest of meal is ready.

While apples and cabbage cook, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Season @bone-in pork chops{20%ounce} all over with salt and pepper. Add to pan
and sear until nicely browned, about ~{3%minutes} per side. Transfer pork to baking
sheet with potatoes and let roast until cooked to desired doneness, ~{5-7%minutes}.
Let pork rest ~{5%minutes} after removing from oven before serving.

Add shallot and remaining garlic to same pan used for pork. Cook until softened,
~{2-3%minutes}. Add @tomato paste{1} and a generous pinch of crushed pepper. Stir
constantly for ~{1%minute}. Add remaining demi-glace and @water{1/2%cup}. Simmer until
thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat and add @butter{1%tablespoon} and
@sour cream{1%tablespoon}. Stir until butter melts.

Give sauce a taste and season with more crushed pepper, if desired. Divide potatoes,
pork, and cabbage with apples between plates and drizzle with sauce.

> TIP: If cabbage has cooled, quickly reheat over medium-low heat before plating.